    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>The night before:</strong></p><p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pods</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife</p><p>Add 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>milk</strong> to a pot over a low heat with 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and the <strong>crushed cardamom pods</strong> and leave to infuse for 4-5 min \u2013 this is your <strong>cardamom infused milk</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-cardamom-and-orange-overnight-oats-and-cranberry-and-apple-oats/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice <strong>half </strong>your<strong> orange[s]</strong> in half (you'll use the rest tomorrow!)</p><p>Add your <strong>oats</strong> to a large bowl (or lidded food-safe container) with your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong>, the juice of the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>orange[s] </strong>and the <strong>cardamom infused milk</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and store, covered, in the fridge overnight \u2013 this is your <strong>cardamom overnight oats</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-cardamom-and-orange-overnight-oats-and-cranberry-and-apple-oats/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Morning 1:</strong></p><p>Crush your <strong>pecan nuts</strong> in its bag with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> (keep them in the bag so you don't lose any!)</p><p>Tip: If you don't have a rolling pin, just chop them roughly!</p><p>Heat a large dry pan over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>crushed pecan nuts</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-cardamom-and-orange-overnight-oats-and-cranberry-and-apple-oats/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>remaining orange[s]</strong> into segments</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-cardamom-and-orange-overnight-oats-and-cranberry-and-apple-oats/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve <strong>half </strong>the <strong>cardamom overnight oats </strong>(you'll use the rest tomorrow!) and top with your <strong>orange segments </strong>and <strong>toasted pecan nuts</strong></p><p>Drizzle with <strong>half </strong>your <strong>maple syrup</strong> (you'll use the rest tomorrow!)</p><p>Dig in!</p><p>Tip: Watch out for any cardamom pods!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-cardamom-and-orange-overnight-oats-and-cranberry-and-apple-oats/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Morning 2:</strong></p><p>Crush your <strong>pistachio nuts</strong> in its bag with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> (keep them in the bag so you don't lose any!)</p><p>Tip: If you don't have a rolling pin, just chop them roughly!</p><p>Heat a large dry pan over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>crushed</strong> <strong>pistachio nuts</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-cardamom-and-orange-overnight-oats-and-cranberry-and-apple-oats/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your <strong>apple[s]</strong> (skin on) and discard the core[s]</p><p>Add the <strong>grated apple </strong>to the <strong>remaining cardamom overnight oats</strong> and mix it all together \u2013 this are your <strong>apple overnight oats</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-cardamom-and-orange-overnight-oats-and-cranberry-and-apple-oats/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>apple overnight oats</strong> and top with your<strong> dried cranberries</strong> and <strong>toasted pistachio nuts</strong></p><p>Drizzle with the <strong>remaining maple syrup</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
